{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnhillshadestylelayer\/hillshademethod"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@property"},{"kind":"text","text":" ("},{"kind":"keyword","text":"nonatomic"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(cs)NSExpression","text":"NSExpression"},{"kind":"text","text":" * "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"hillshadeMethod"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}],"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["occ"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The default value of this property is an expression that evaluates to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"standard"},{"type":"text","text":". Set this property to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" to reset it to the default value."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can set this property to an expression containing any of the following:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Constant ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNHillshadeMethod"},{"text":" values","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Any of the following constant string values:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"standard"},{"text":": The legacy hillshade method.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"basic"},{"text":": Basic hillshade. Uses a simple physics model where the reflected","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"light intensity is proportional to the cosine of the angle between the incident","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"light and the surface normal. Similar to GDAL’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gdaldem"},{"text":" default algorithm.","type"